gineering</meta-value></custom-meta><custom-meta><meta-name>journal-subject-collection</meta-name><meta-value>Engineering</meta-value></custom-meta><custom-meta><meta-name>open-access</meta-name><meta-value>false</meta-value></custom-meta></custom-meta-group></article-meta></front><body><p id="Par101">As the Guest editors of this special issue on selected papers from ESDA 2021, it gives us great pleasure to present a collection of selected papers from the 4th international conference on Energy Systems, Drives and Automations (ESDA2021), held in Kolkata, West Bengal, India, in 30th &amp; 31st December 2021.</p><p id="Par1">The articles featured in this special issue of Microsystem Technologies have been selected after a rigorous peer-review process and cover a diverse range of topics that are of great importance to the research community. Many senior professors, scientists, and research scholars who have contributed their valuable insights and expertise in the field of Electrical, Mechanical, and Electronic research and applications. They offer new insights, innovative solutions, and critical evaluations of existing knowledge. It is our hope that this special issue will serve as a valuable resource for researchers, practitioners, and students who are interested in this field.</p><p id="Par2">The papers are categorized into different sections like: Power System Operation and Control, Power Electronics and Energy Conversion, Renewable Energy Systems, Solar Energy, Bio Mass Energy, Electrical Vehicle Systems, Fuel Cells, Smart Grid Technologies, Micro Grid Technologies, Tidal Energy, Wind Energy Electric Conversion Systems, soft computing and optimization techniques, Hybrid Energy Systems, Energy Conservation and Auditing, Energy Storage and Battery Management, FACTS, HVDC and Power Quality, Parallel, grid and cloud computing, Micro Hydel Systems, Fault Detection, Isolation and Recovery, Power Factor and Efficiency Improvement, Conventional and Special Electrical Machines, Application of Control Theory, Industrial Drives, High Voltage Engineering, PLC and its Programming, Circuits with Mechanical Feedback and Speed Control Circuits.</p><p id="Par3">We would like to express our gratitude to the authors who have contributed their valuable work to this special issue, as well as to the reviewers who have provided their insightful comments and suggestions. Without their contributions, this special issue would not have been possible.</p><p id="Par4">Finally, we would like to thank the editorial team for their support throughout the process of creating this special issue. Their dedication and hard work have made this project a success. I hope that readers will find this special issue informative, engaging, and thought-provoking, and that it will inspire further research and development in the field.</p><p id="Par5">Prof. Pradip Kumar Sadhu,</p><p id="Par6">Guest Editor of Special Issue</p><p id="Par7">Dr. Pranab Kumar Mondal,</p><p id="Par8">Guest Editor of Special Issue</p><p id="Par9">Prof. Dulal Acharjee.</p><p id="Par10">Lead Guest Editor of Special Issue</p><p id="Par11">Microsystem Technologies</p></body><back><notes notes-type="Misc"><title>Publisher’s Note</title><p>Springer Nature remains neutral with regard to jurisdictional claims in published maps and institutional affiliations.</p></notes></back></article></records><facets><facet name="subject"><facet-value count="1">Electronics and Microelectronics, Instrumentation</facet-value><facet-value count="1">Engineering</facet-value><facet-value count="1">Mechanical Engineering</facet-value><facet-value count="1">Nanotechnology</facet-value></facet><facet name="keyword"/><facet name="pub"><facet-value count="1">Microsystem Technologies</facet-value></facet><facet name="year"><facet-value count="1">2023</facet-value></facet><facet name="country"><facet-value count="1">India</facet-value></facet><facet name="type"><facet-value count="1">Journal</facet-value></facet></facets></respons